            <title>[SOLR-6651] Fix wrong logging in waitForReplicasToComeUp</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6651</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;            log.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Waiting until we see more replicas up &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; shard &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + shardId + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;: total=&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
              + slices.getReplicasMap().size() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; found=&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + found
              + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; timeoutin=&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + (timeoutAt - &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.nanoTime() / (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt;)(10^9)) + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ms&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That code isn&apos;t calculating the timeout correctly in the logging statement.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
